Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["05 Hexagon and Triangle", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"0570cc4a-85c0-4988-a0d4-2a62c6dd0d65"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook checks the regular-hexagon coefficient Z(phi, xi), its phi=0 \
and phi=15 degree limits, and the equilateral-triangle formulas.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a80e26a5-8734-41a0-badc-033abbd66419"],

Cell["\<\
Reader map: first define the hexagon prefactor Z(phi, xi) in Eq. (S11), then \
take the special limits phi = 0 and phi = 15 degrees to recover Eqs. (S12) \
and (S13). The same notebook then checks the equilateral-triangle formulas in \
SI Sec. VIII.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a57a7a06-0426-4e7a-a371-ffec580eaa94"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Hexagon and Triangle Checks", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"948626ce-8416-40cd-8140-92e5012f1014"],

Cell["\<\
The numerical roots are the first few magic sizes xi_m for the hexagon. For \
the triangle, the phi = 0 result is obtained by direct integration, while the \
phi = 30 degree expression is checked by substituting xi = Sqrt[3] k.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"76b0258b-9dcd-4845-8929-c0c2a5f5bd63"],

